GOSH Announcements 14.05.2024 23:36:38
In reply to this message
Mitja has left Everscale. Completely.

GOSH co-founder announced today, that he does not have any financial assets left on Everscale blockchain. The full text of the announcement reads as following:

"Today, I performed my last transaction on the blockchain called "Everscale." I no longer have, nor will I have, any assets in this network. I have not participated in any Everscale developments for two years now. Despite the fact that Everscale developers are still trying to implement the ideas and technical solutions proposed and developed by me, including solutions used in other networks based on code developed by the TON Labs technical team under my direction, I have no connection to these developments, nor to the technical modifications made to the design of these developments. To make it completely clear, I repeat ‚Äî my participation in the technical implementation and design of the Everscale project ended two years ago, and my involvement in any network management processes ceased when it was still called Free TON and aimed for decentralization."

The screenshot above illustrates the final asset relocation to Ethereum mainnet.

In reply to this message
https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2024/05/15/brothers-accused-of-25m-ethereum-exploit-as-us-reveals-fraud-charges/

The Pepaire-Bueno brothers exploited a bug in MEV-boost's code that allowed them to preview the content of blocks before they were officially delivered to validators, according to the indictment.
The brothers created 16 Ethereum validators and targeted three specific traders who operated MEV bots, the indictment said. They used bait transactions to figure out how those bots traded, lured the bots to one of their validators which was validating a new block and basically tricked these bots into proposing certain transactions. The brothers allegedly frontran the bots on certain trades and also used their validator to "tamper with" the new block by sending a false digital signature that gave them access to the block's full contents and replaced "lure transactions" with "tampered transactions." In those tampered transactions, the brothers allegedly sold illiquid cryptocurrencies they had tricked the victims' trading bots into placing buy orders for.

Integrity Certificates Partners With rePLANET to Build End-To-End Decentralized Pipeline for Biodiversity Credits Powered by GOSH

Partnership will offer range of instruments for rePLANET‚Äôs nature based credits issuance, priced at upwards of $95Mn., assuring widely established scientific methodology and decentralization to address the biodiversity crisis

As reported today by leading climate news and intelligence publication Carbon Pulse, ‚Äî the companies are developing a decentralised peer-to-peer exchange that should enable users to trade assets through blockchain transaction via the GOSH platform, without the opacity of an intermediary.

Earlier this week Dow Jones first weekly Biodiversity Market Report, stated that 11,683,980 credits are listed in rePLANET‚Äôs portfolio of projects, priced at an estimated total value of $95,015,300 if generated at posted price levels, is evidence of the maturation of the nature capital market.

Integrity Certificates, a nature value chain certification partner, and GOSH, a highly scalable free-to-use decentralized version control platform, today announced a partnership with rePLANET, a nature project developer with more than 20 years of infield experience, to build an end-to-end decentralized pipeline for nature based credits.
The partnership allows rePLANET to leverage decentralization to ensure the integrity of large-scale biodiversity projects across the whole value chain, with scientific peer review verification, and certification at scale, unlocking necessary regenerative financing. As part of the agreement, Integrity Certificates assures the verification, issuance and registry services for rePLANET biodiversity credits.

‚ÄúBuyers don‚Äôt need promises, they need guarantees,‚Äù said Director of Strategy at rePLANET Dan Exton.

The solution developed by Swiss based Integrity Certificates in partnership with GOSH and UK based rePLANET ensures verified biodiversity gains using GOSH running on the Acki Nacki blockchain

–§–æ—Ä–º–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏—è

1. –ê—Å–∏–Ω—Ö—Ä–æ–Ω–Ω–∞—è –º–æ–¥–µ–ª—å: \(\mathcal{M} = (S, Q, R)\), –≥–¥–µ \(S\) - –º–Ω–æ–∂–µ—Å—Ç–≤–æ —Å–æ—Å—Ç–æ—è–Ω–∏–π, \(Q\) - –º–Ω–æ–∂–µ—Å—Ç–≤–æ –∑–∞–ø—Ä–æ—Å–æ–≤, \(R\) - –º–Ω–æ–∂–µ—Å—Ç–≤–æ –æ—Ç–≤–µ—Ç–æ–≤.

–¢–µ–æ—Ä–µ–º–∞ (—Ñ–æ—Ä–º–∞–ª–∏–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–Ω–∞—è –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—è CAP-—Ç–µ–æ—Ä–µ–º—ã):

–í –∞—Å–∏–Ω—Ö—Ä–æ–Ω–Ω–æ–π —Å–∏—Å—Ç–µ–º–µ \(\mathcal{M}\) –Ω–µ–≤–æ–∑–º–æ–∂–Ω–æ –æ–¥–Ω–æ–≤—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω–Ω–æ –æ–±–µ—Å–ø–µ—á–∏—Ç—å:
1. –°–æ–≥–ª–∞—Å–æ–≤–∞–Ω–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—å.

1. –í—ã–±–∏—Ä–∞–µ—Ç —Å–ª—É—á–∞–π–Ω–æ–µ –ø—Ä–∏–≤–∞—Ç–Ω–æ–µ —á–∏—Å–ª–æ b
2. –í—ã—á–∏—Å–ª—è–µ—Ç –ø—É–±–ª–∏—á–Ω–æ–µ —á–∏—Å–ª–æ B = g^b mod p
3. –û—Ç–ø—Ä–∞–≤–ª—è–µ—Ç B –ê–ª–∏—Å–µ —á–µ—Ä–µ–∑ —á–∞—Ç

–®–∞–≥ 3: –í—ã—á–∏—Å–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ –æ–±—â–µ–≥–æ —Å–µ–∫—Ä–µ—Ç–∞

–ê–ª–∏—Å–∞:
1. –ü–æ–ª—É—á–∞–µ—Ç B –æ—Ç –ë–æ–±–∞
2. –í—ã—á–∏—Å–ª—è–µ—Ç –æ–±—â–∏–π —Å–µ–∫—Ä–µ—Ç S = B^a mod p

–ë–æ–±:
1. –ü–æ–ª—É—á–∞–µ—Ç A –æ—Ç –ê–ª–∏—Å—ã
2. –í—ã—á–∏—Å–ª—è–µ—Ç –æ–±—â–∏–π —Å–µ–∫—Ä–µ—Ç S = A^b mod p

–¢–µ–ø–µ—Ä—å —É –ê–ª–∏—Å—ã –∏ –ë–æ–±–∞ –µ—Å—Ç—å –æ–±—â–∏–π —Å–µ–∫—Ä–µ—Ç–Ω—ã–π –∫–ª—é—á S, –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä—ã–π –í–æ–ª–∞–Ω–¥ –Ω–µ –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç —É–∑–Ω–∞—Ç—å, —Ç–∞–∫ –∫–∞–∫ —É –Ω–µ–≥–æ –Ω–µ—Ç –ø—Ä–∏–≤–∞—Ç–Ω—ã—Ö —á–∏—Å–µ–ª a –∏ b

–í–æ—Ç –ø—Ä–∏–º–µ—Ä —Ä–µ–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏–∏ –ø—Ä–æ—Ç–æ–∫–æ–ª–∞ –î–∏—Ñ—Ñ–∏-–•–µ–ª–ª–º–∞–Ω–∞:

import random

# –ü—É–±–ª–∏—á–Ω—ã–µ –ø–∞—Ä–∞–º–µ—Ç—Ä—ã (–¥–æ–ª–∂–Ω—ã –±—ã—Ç—å —Å–æ–≥–ª–∞—Å–æ–≤–∞–Ω—ã –º–µ–∂–¥—É –ê–ª–∏—Å–æ–π –∏ –ë–æ–±–æ–º)
p = 23  # –ø—Ä–æ—Å—Ç–æ–µ —á–∏—Å–ª–æ
g = 5   # –≥–µ–Ω–µ—Ä–∞—Ç–æ—Ä

# –ê–ª–∏—Å–∞ –≥–µ–Ω–µ—Ä–∏—Ä—É–µ—Ç —Å–≤–æ–∏ –∫–ª—é—á–∏
a = random.randint(1, p-1)  # –ø—Ä–∏–≤–∞—Ç–Ω–æ–µ —á–∏—Å–ª–æ
A = pow(g, a, p)            # –ø—É–±–ª–∏—á–Ω–æ–µ —á–∏—Å–ª–æ

# –ë–æ–± –≥–µ–Ω–µ—Ä–∏—Ä—É–µ—Ç —Å–≤–æ–∏ –∫–ª—é—á–∏
b = random.randint(1, p-1)  # –ø—Ä–∏–≤–∞—Ç–Ω–æ–µ —á–∏—Å–ª–æ
B = pow(g, b, p)            # –ø—É–±–ª–∏—á–Ω–æ–µ —á–∏—Å–ª–æ

# –ê–ª–∏—Å–∞ –∏ –ë–æ–± –æ–±–º–µ–Ω–∏–≤–∞—é—Ç—Å—è –ø—É–±–ª–∏—á–Ω—ã–º–∏ –∫–ª—é—á–∞–º–∏
# –ê–ª–∏—Å–∞ –æ—Ç–ø—Ä–∞–≤–ª—è–µ—Ç A –ë–æ–±—É, –∞ –ë–æ–± –æ—Ç–ø—Ä–∞–≤–ª—è–µ—Ç B –ê–ª–∏—Å–µ

# –ê–ª–∏—Å–∞ –≤—ã—á–∏—Å–ª—è–µ—Ç –æ–±—â–∏–π —Å–µ–∫—Ä–µ—Ç
S_alice = pow(B, a, p)

# –ë–æ–± –≤—ã—á–∏—Å–ª—è–µ—Ç –æ–±—â–∏–π —Å–µ–∫—Ä–µ—Ç
S_bob = pow(A, b, p)

print("–û–±—â–∏–π —Å–µ–∫—Ä–µ—Ç (–ê–ª–∏—Å–∞):", S_alice)
print("–û–±—â–∏–π —Å–µ–∫—Ä–µ—Ç (–ë–æ–±):", S_bob)

I apologize for the issues you‚Äôve experienced. Let‚Äôs clarify the situation regarding Everscale tokens and Bithumb.

In December 2023, Everscale and Bithumb took joint measures in response to suspicious trading activity with the WEVER (Wrapped EVER ERC-20) token. They decided to allow the withdrawal of old WEVER tokens from Bithumb, while keeping deposits closed and permanently suspending trading of the old WEVER token. This decision was aimed at ensuring compliance with Korean cryptocurrency regulations and the decisions of EverDAO. Additionally, Everscale worked on listing a new Wrapped EVER ERC-20 token on Bithumb, which depended on the exchange's discretion [[‚ùû]](https://blog.everscale.network/other/everscale-network-and-bithumb-exchange-announce-joint-measures-for-old-wever-token-swap) [[‚ùû]](https://blog.everscale.network/other/ever-fully-back-on-majority-of-exchanges-as-network-moves-forward).

During this process, old tokens were swapped and burned, which helped reintegrate EVER on major exchanges such as MEXC, Gate.io, Coinone, HTX, and KuCoin. This step was crucial in stabilizing the situation and allowing the network to continue its growth [[‚ùû]](https://blog.everscale.network/other/ever-fully-back-on-majority-of-exchanges-as-network-moves-forward) [[‚ùû]](https://blog.everscale.network/other?page=1).

We understand that these measures may have caused inconvenience to token holders, and we apologize for any difficulties faced. All Bithumb users holding old WEVER tokens were provided with instructions and support from the Everscale team for the token swap [[‚ùû]](https://blog.everscale.network/other/everscale-network-and-bithumb-exchange-announce-joint-measures-for-old-wever-token-swap) [[‚ùû]](https://blog.everscale.network/other/ever-fully-back-on-majority-of-exchanges-as-network-moves-forward).
